com.safenetinc.luna
Class LunaTokenObject

java.lang.Object
  com.safenetinc.luna.LunaTokenObject

public class LunaTokenObject
extends Object

An instance of this class represents an object stored on a Luna token.

The LunaTokenObject encapsulates the token object handle and implements a number of methods for accessing the object. It also manages sessions for the token object.

This class is intended for internal Luna provider use only. The APIs may change without warning. Use at your own risk

GetLargeAttribute

public byte[] GetLargeAttribute(long attribute)
Returns the value of the requested attribute as a byte array. This is useful for data such as large primes. The data is returned as it is stored on the HSM, so if this method is used to retrieve CK_ULONG values they will need to be converted from little-endian to big-endian in order to be interpreted properly as numbers. In that case use of the GetSmallAttribute method is preferred.

Parameters:
attribute - The PKCS11 CKA_* id of the attribute
Returns:
The attribute value as a byte array
Throws:
LunaException - If this object is uninitialized

value - The value to assign to the given attribute
Returns:
The PKCS11 CKR return code
Throws:
LunaException - If this object is uninitialized

GetSmallAttribute

public long GetSmallAttribute(long attribute)
Returns the requested attribute value of the given key, interpreted as a PKCS CK_ULONG. The HSM uses 4 bytes to store a CK_ULONG, so the most-significant 4 bytes of the long returned by this method will be unused.

If the attribute being requested is not actually a CK_ULONG on the HSM, then this method will return a numerical interpretation of the first 4 bytes of the attribute.

Parameters:
attribute - The PKCS11 CKA_* id of the attribute
Returns:
The attribute value as a long value
Throws:
LunaException - If this object is uninitialized

SetSmallAttribute

public long SetSmallAttribute(long attribute,
                              long value)
Sets the value of the given attribute, as a PKCS CK_ULONG. The HSM uses 4 bytes to store a CK_ULONG, so only the least-significant 4 bytes of the data supplied to this method will be used.

Parameters:
attribute - The PKCS11 CKA_* id of the attribute
value - The value to assign to the given attribute
Returns:
The PKCS11 CKR return code of the operation
Throws:
LunaException - If this object is uninitialized

Gets the boolean value of the given attribute. If the attribute is not actually a boolean on the HSM (i.e. not a CK_BOOL attribute), then this method will return a boolean interpretation of the first byte of the attribute -- false if it is 0x00, true otherwise.

GetFingerprint

public byte[] GetFingerprint()
Returns the fingerprint of the HSM object wrapped by this object. The fingerprint is a byte array that contains a SHA-1 hash of various attributes of the object. It is exceedingly unlikely that any two objects will share a fingerprint unless the objects are true duplicates of each other.

Returns:
The fingerprint as a byte array

MakePersistent

public void MakePersistent(String alias)
If this object is currently a session object, it is persisted with the given alias. Duplicate aliases are allowed on the HSM. If this method is called on an object that is already persistent, one of two things will happen:
  • If the new alias is the same as the old alias, nothing is changed
  • If the new alias is different from the old alias, the object is duplicated. This instance of LunaTokenObject is changed to point to the new object on the HSM. The old object is not removed from the HSM

Parameters:
alias - The alias to assign to the HSM object
Throws:
LunaException - if the LunaTokenObject object is uninitialized, if alias is null, or if alias points to a non-existent key
LunaPartitionFullException - if the HSM partition does not have enough storage space to create the new token object
